Before running the application make sure that you have the expo app installed on a moblie device. The app is avaiable for both andriod and IOS devices.

Steps tp run the application: 
1) Download the zip file to a chose directory
2) Open up terminal application on a windows laptop/ desktop
3) cd to the Climate-Change-App folder
4) Once the Climate-Change-App ensure that react native is installed in the Climate-Change-App directory the followig links provides guidance on how to install: https://reactnative.dev/docs/environment-setup and https://docs.expo.dev/tutorial/create-your-first-app/
5) Once all the necessary software is installed run 'npm start' or 'npx expo start' to run the application. A QR code will appear in the terminal, scan this using the expo go app on your mobile device to allow the app to run on your mobile device.


RUN THIS BEFORE STARTING THE ANY OF THE WORDLE GAME MODES
Steps to run Python Flask Server:
1) Ensure that python is installed on your machine link to install python: https://www.python.org/downloads/windows/
2) Open another tab/terminal window and cd to the directory of BackendDev and type 'python app.py' to begin running the python flask server 
3) To see the json file produced click on the link showing the host url for the server and add '/climate-news' to the end of it.
4) If you run into any issues with imports install any of the following libraires: 
- Flask: https://pypi.org/project/Flask/
- requests: https://pypi.org/project/requests/
- bs4: https://pypi.org/project/beautifulsoup4/
- spacy: https://pypi.org/project/spacy/
- TfidVectorizer : https://pypi.org/project/sklearn-features/
- https://pypi.org/project/numpy/



RUN THIS BEFORE STARTING THE WORDLE MULTIPLAYER GAME MODE
Steps to run Python SocketIO Server:
1) Ensure that python is installed on your machine link to install python: https://www.python.org/downloads/windows/
2) Open another tab/terminal window and cd to MultiPlayerBackendDev
3) Then type the command 'venv\Scripts\activate' to activate ther virtual environment.
4) The type python MultiplayerApp.py to run the environment.
5) A host link should be shown, which can be clicked showing a message on the browser that the server is currently running
6) If you run into any issues with imports install any of the following libraires:
- Flask: https://pypi.org/project/Flask/
- SocketIO: https://pypi.org/project/python-socketio/
- uuid: https://pypi.org/project/uuid/
- threading: https://pypi.org/project/thread/
- time: https://pypi.org/project/TIME-python/